theorem Topology.interiorClosureInteriorClosure_subset_interiorClosure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  -- First, `interior (closure A)` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h₁ : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
    interior_subset
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h₂ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono h₁
  -- Finally, taking interiors preserves inclusions.
  exact interior_mono h₂
